    <title>BASF and Nuritas Use AI to Develop New Food Ingredients</title>
    <link>http://www.powderbulksolids.com/news/BASF-and-Nuritas-Use-AI-to-Develop-New-Food-Ingredients-01-23-2017</link>
    <description>
          &lt;span class=&quot;date-display-single&quot; property=&quot;dc:date&quot; datatype=&quot;xsd:dateTime&quot; content=&quot;2017-01-23T00:00:00-07:00&quot;&gt;January 23, 2017&lt;/span&gt;    

          &lt;img typeof=&quot;foaf:Image&quot; src=&quot;http://www.powderbulksolids.com/sites/powderbulksolids.com/files/styles/medium/public/news/images/15637895469_065426634a_z_0.jpg?itok=hagSLnSt&quot; width=&quot;220&quot; height=&quot;165&quot; alt=&quot;BASF Human Nutrition and Nuritas are teaming up to develop new peptide food ingredients that offer health benefits. Image courtesy of Flickr user Michael Stern&quot; title=&quot;BASF Human Nutrition and Nuritas are teaming up to develop new peptide food ingredients that offer health benefits. Image courtesy of Flickr user Michael Stern&quot; /&gt;    

          &lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.newtrition.basf.com/&quot;&gt;BASF&amp;rsquo;s Human Nutrition business&lt;/a&gt; is partnering with Dublin, Ireland-based biotechnology company &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.nuritas.com/&quot;&gt;Nuritas&lt;/a&gt; to discover and bring to market new bioactive peptide food ingredients that offer health benefits using the Irish company&amp;rsquo;s proprietary artificial intelligence (AI) and DNA analysis technology, the companies announced in Jan. 18 joint press release.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;ldquo;The ingredients that will be brought to the market are going to be truly life-changing,&amp;rdquo; said Emmet Browne, chief executive officer of Nuritas in the release.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Nuritas&amp;rsquo; technology uses AI, deep computations, and DNA analysis to &amp;ldquo;rapidly and efficiently&amp;rdquo; predict and help utilize peptides within food, short chains of amino acids occurring naturally that can offer health benefits by signaling certain molecules in the body.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The first component of the deal gives BASF an exclusive, royalty-based license to commercialize one of Nuritas&amp;rsquo; existing peptides for use across a number of applications, the companies said in the release. The second half of the collaboration involves discovering new peptides based on health issues that offer strategic importance to BASF&amp;rsquo;s customers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;ldquo;We think Nuritas is bringing a truly unique and innovative approach in addition to the actual ingredient on the table,&amp;rdquo; said Francois Scheffler, head of BASF&amp;rsquo;s Global Human Nutrition and Pharma Solutions businesses in a statement. &amp;ldquo;Therefore our cooperation with them makes us as BASF an even stronger partner for our customers, to fully support them in delivering highly efficacious solutions under the Newtrition brand &amp;ndash; which means delivering the right nutrients to the right people at the right time.&amp;rdquo;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Nuritas was founded in 2014 by Dr. Nora Khaldi, a mathematician and computational biologist, to discover food ingredients that offer health benefits.&lt;/p&gt;
