    <title>AkzoNobel Opens Powder Coatings Plant in China</title>
    <link>http://www.powderbulksolids.com/news/AkzoNobel-Opens-Powder-Coatings-Plant-in-China-01-20-2017</link>
    <description>
          &lt;span class=&quot;date-display-single&quot; property=&quot;dc:date&quot; datatype=&quot;xsd:dateTime&quot; content=&quot;2017-01-20T00:00:00-07:00&quot;&gt;January 20, 2017&lt;/span&gt;    

          &lt;img typeof=&quot;foaf:Image&quot; src=&quot;http://www.powderbulksolids.com/sites/powderbulksolids.com/files/styles/medium/public/news/images/gh_8572.jpg?itok=sbphOIDE&quot; width=&quot;220&quot; height=&quot;127&quot; alt=&quot;AkzoNobel&amp;#039;s new powder coatings facility in China. Image courtesy of AkzoNobel&quot; title=&quot;AkzoNobel&amp;#039;s new powder coatings facility in China. Image courtesy of AkzoNobel&quot; /&gt;    

          &lt;p&gt;A new &amp;euro;11 million powder coating plant was opened by AkzoNobel &amp;nbsp;in Chengdu, China, the company&amp;rsquo;s sixth facility producing powder coatings in the country, the Dutch company announced Jan. 17.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;ldquo;The opening of our Chengdu production site will strengthen our position as the global leader and China&amp;rsquo;s largest powder coatings supplier,&amp;rdquo; a statement by Contrad Keijzer, a member of AkzoNobel&amp;rsquo;s executive committee that is responsible for its performance coatings business. &amp;ldquo;It will allow us to leverage the strong growth that we see in the western provinces of China, furthering our organic growth momentum.&amp;rdquo;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Serving local automotive, construction, furniture, and IT industries, the new facility features equipment to fully recycle waste water generated in operations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;According to the company, the factory&amp;rsquo;s opening is a result of the Chinese government&amp;rsquo;s Western Development Policy, noting that many manufacturers are opening sites in the region, including a large car manufacturing center.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;ldquo;We are going through a rapid change in western China and that is generating more demand for our business,&amp;rdquo; said AkzoNobel&amp;rsquo;s Powder Coatings unit in north Asia. &amp;ldquo;The new Chengdu site is an important investment in the region and will enhance our support to local customers, particularly, particularly those in the automotive industry.&amp;rdquo;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;AkzoNobel is also constructing a facility billed as &amp;ldquo;the largest powder coatings plant in the world&amp;rdquo; in Changzhou, China with a projected opening in October 2017.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: &#039;Helvetica Neue&#039;, Arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;For more articles, news, and equipment reviews,&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.powderbulksolids.com/equipment-zones&quot; style=&quot;margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; font-family: &#039;Helvetica Neue&#039;, Arial, sans-serif; line-height: inherit; color: rgb(3, 98, 193); cursor: pointer; text-decoration: none;&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;visit our Equipment Zones&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
    
